{"id": "0870ea4e55c70b01f9ddc0c44e78b0e8b7865feb7f693c2cebf6ea0f63744566", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:0", "text": "The Common Tab provides settings shared between all renderers in Maya. Note that this configuration is visible after setting RenderMan as the renderer or opening the settings from the RenderMan menu."}
{"id": "8377a9b882a7feffc964c005619d9934727bec35bc80677777922300a0de35fe", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:1", "text": "You will find most of this functionality has been moved to the"}
{"id": "a91ff5ea4bfc5e7e71d93d9b2f1fdcca1bef559793ab42694702378ccd2e69f9", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:8", "text": "Workspace Tab"}
{"id": "34579aed1d04c94a03daa67ae81748c8b28616741da66813af48e43b151dd878", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:3", "text": "to simplify selections. Below is an explanation of older options we do not support and many have been removed from the RenderMan Common Tab."}
{"id": "62fa5a5b0d3c318835a213e22a4b335c42515443d598741d0413e8c47f9ecf67", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:4", "text": "Path"}
{"id": "9887b138510f21109c9e205efcf7c49deaafed7aa471f94ed4fe8e780264ba58", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:5", "text": "Does not apply, if this is visible, toggle your renderer selection away and back to RenderMan to refresh."}
{"id": "ca4c37cb4476ae2b0cba406f2d2ba86941c15e9d3a169ed2feb37fd0b9fe07b7", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:6", "text": "File Name"}
{"id": "9003e8a88a966425bd1e55ba5b20e09b2b30af754141d9791f31a16e23decad1", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:7", "text": "Does not apply, please use the"}
{"id": "a00de5c51084a6d5bc9368dd1e1819e4524bbe48c07bff174a6bf1f9ac563257", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:9", "text": "for naming using convenient tokens."}
{"id": "06894274016bb7385e9c2dc45278071dadc029f505dc03028c4c464aac549c0e", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:47", "text": "Image Size"}
{"id": "0dd882cec758536d1ed220ad40f7dad3a9a2b07b07b96598c0c4ef4e480d8f60", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:11", "text": "Displays the resolution (generally in pixels and inches)."}
{"id": "9554b9b9a4d8cf35a0c2bdbb199d7f1480344e7e95f27572fa7241f2a8976531", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:12", "text": "Color Management"}
{"id": "ce9a451e39dde4a0c48798a4a39765c0e3e35cfaee252e825d87eaf60ac2f8ab", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:13", "text": "RenderMan does not support the Output Transform setting. However, view"}
{"id": "0568f242ae73a64fcef73b4333657ea5974829b8bc9ef91ec9b5e6d3562bf610", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:14", "text": "remapping"}
{"id": "b7ffdd60db5c429ed308ebc89c870991cd56afd485ff06f8d63848c2c836f03a", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:15", "text": "is available in \"it\"."}
{"id": "aec78b33190d3e4218c8302ec3d9e4562e965bc7f712908fc8f6883ca8dcac53", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:16", "text": "File Output"}
{"id": "1def6dc66ed97b44fbabdc8c8106b9950917c8dc2066749886d5b6d16dafe2f8", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:17", "text": "The name of rendered image files can be composed of up to three elements: file name, frame number, and file format."}
{"id": "113b100d0c76247ee71490d1fe67a7e5128b77c00ac082e07675a5f755ff7fd8", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:18", "text": "File Name Prefix"}
{"id": "4aa19524716fbc0e21ebebb770be5f6ebb41c91a8cb47a1fc4789a18b7ff607d", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:19", "text": "Determines the base name for rendered images."}
{"id": "e44b829d507a8d2931686ee7ebd0fba00da0ffb41834e70b14174104c4dbbf00", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:20", "text": "Image Format"}
{"id": "5a179c74a3845fe6ea7b229ba684d531b476ca18e9d0b3d2c46ca40ef6b1f727", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:21", "text": "Does not apply, the"}
{"id": "1071b7c9d289d7fd7ed392d1123de7338323b1195c948c2d47328798a8acfdf2", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:22", "text": "AOVs tab"}
{"id": "34a164a1eb2259b63bef934175b25202f67af475b988a3c21c5fadad9f96b396", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:23", "text": "sets the display driver."}
{"id": "278b1b2a9c84730f37f6d36630281494544a27e37168b4c6e45859667777f609", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:24", "text": "Compression"}
{"id": "3e2dc2a227a7ed69d28e7d2fea4c228d08285dc206761efaeed84f6f1d3665fc", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:25", "text": "Does not apply, the AOVs tab sets the compression in the Display Driver"}
{"id": "281552662bb2eb31dd9b354c3fd4752389512cdd90d4a39010cbe4b3280ba29c", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:26", "text": "Frame/Animation Ext"}
{"id": "9ceb6f3c7b439690968afd4ee2fb49d690db589b310442d0d3822253d8e98ea1", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:27", "text": "The format used to name output images."}
{"id": "699aac50ace6936ef031e23e8e09cb7b8d961106bf81e29cf1119cdd2909af31", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:28", "text": "Frame Padding"}
{"id": "e40c3b136e80c3244c40a86f9875b3d95417586cf2ae96aa244fc3bb98c87585", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:29", "text": "Does not apply, use the Workspace Tab to set this with the tokens as explained on the documentation page."}
{"id": "f280af8d45b939d4cc28400066b9d5cc8845b39175cdd9cae1306f882afa22cf", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:30", "text": "Framebuffer/Naming Scheme"}
{"id": "93bffccdc89563fe3579b212259a4646675b53d70f05952cfee95cc3c70e6324", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:31", "text": "Does not apply to RfM, these are set in the AOVs tab"}
{"id": "247bcb8f7f96850b9361a9078bc7e062900770709a18f8bc7eb88368750b94a6", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:32", "text": "Use Custom Extension"}
{"id": "0664669e5c98fbb86a34cf44c3f4e6ac434b6b8cdc4d76fb8a9a6d9173e6f27f", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:33", "text": "Does not apply to RfM, use the Workspace tab as mentioned above."}
{"id": "ca3df76d61a199feca6935f7ac6d7ecc310022a9b7431adc5ede05be2bd99e1f", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:34", "text": "Frame Range"}
{"id": "756ce5d84f54cf57d468bc8f79c7a0116620d9a621ec4c708a579ef3a68f3ed3", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:35", "text": "Start Frame, End Frame"}
{"id": "3860d03e4d8648eb4324a8ef97c1d934afef7e299ef93632afc4ca603d180df2", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:36", "text": "Specifies the first and last frames to render. Frame/Animation Ext must be set to an option containing # to enable these parameters, otherwise a single frame will be used."}
{"id": "42f8569cf62c4500e24a8e4c8580d2e07a311f7f7706dd05ded2c26fb69501a5", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:37", "text": "By Frame"}
{"id": "404af84b375d76e1166f18bbdaa107b46c8f8037f5a19b6439a78b2c0c225539", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:38", "text": "The increment between the output names of rendered frames. By Frame is only available if Frame/Animation Ext is set to an option containing #."}
{"id": "c4246fb181cd234fef7e28d183ca6874b550367c172214cc3172141041d864c2", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:39", "text": "Renderable Cameras"}
{"id": "b99c139c23388b801d129828bb903f3d1b676a34312ef6764e91110a88e69c8a", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:40", "text": "Renderable Camera"}
{"id": "69b7ecbb497374b2bfae5faeff96d9449964e05e6b72c925f9ae5e01233e1ec0", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:41", "text": "Select your render camera from this list."}
{"id": "1fbd4f9e67b146370fcf2de45cc4df9e24e998136bac3ce39947a2e61d5eb708", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:42", "text": "If your scene has only one renderable camera (for example, the perspective camera), whatever camera is selected in this drop-down list becomes the renderable camera. In other words, the newly selected camera becomes the renderable one in your scene (the default perspective camera becomes unrenderable)."}
{"id": "c2ef8c5cc90dd981cec57896c655a9f92e4151b9001e305a02d0cdd94eacdc1c", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:43", "text": "Alpha Channel (Mask)"}
{"id": "a489fd38c4cb6acc9f6d67ffd92be2f40814c02f3f5a2e7c700d5ae65d9afe5f", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:44", "text": "Determines whether rendered images contain a mask channel."}
{"id": "1917acbda50dd1ed036e6b7222073a4e5bf6145a9a9fd7fe5ddb8725eaf07ff0", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:45", "text": "Depth Channel (Z Depth)"}
{"id": "b1ce632b25311594d4f660d721b5e53afbb147222cdff72039f0277b5933d351", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:46", "text": "Determines whether rendered images contain a depth channel. Preferred to use the AOVs tab to specify __depth or Z."}
{"id": "954f93fe1c66ae447f4d9e75eb0dc5a32f3a45dfc1cfb6df391a9d5947a97d10", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:48", "text": "Presets"}
{"id": "0ffa9a57b652c6a8cc8a431246d1ec63128a1e259d9de8f636b6ff8000bcc0bc", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:49", "text": "Choose a resolution for your output images based on a selection of industry standards."}
{"id": "31396264ed2e39ed532cd866ca9e500d4fdef1f59fe53ebbbfb23af1e208494a", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:50", "text": "Maintain Width/Height Ratio"}
{"id": "e51aa019f2e61f65ed7b0afce77a290e6d4cc4f078b96b1a7251698a0b7850b3", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:51", "text": "If this box is checked, custom resolutions will maintain a locked ratio between height and width. By disabling this parameter, any numbers may be enter for image resolution."}
{"id": "fc1c0045238ff972ae17ad1973bab18e19efb95122384f443f2bdcaebca44f01", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:52", "text": "Width/Height"}
{"id": "397373e210b1c9b02164a5870e55066a1de7ca103742af06de21ddfdfb34a133", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:53", "text": "For custom resolutions, enter the desired resolutions here."}
{"id": "946301e13f263c160da9f277ca62b5dc401792878346955fc0b8a611a7d03d10", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:54", "text": "Size Units"}
{"id": "c9cd29d6e2156f0fce1d75737be49d8283cac966dc18b67da68d45ea8de2a680", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:55", "text": "Select an appropriate unit of measurement."}
{"id": "a2cf4038f1d7791c18546ee42e62f01600197c32d50432db8a444b2ea957b9db", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:57", "text": "Set the rendered resolution of your image."}
{"id": "1a0ded975cf532c2be53f90aebd0a8564852fc7d7082bfbfcfba4b71504f555d", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:58", "text": "Resolution Units"}
{"id": "a78d63d18fc3c614ce24085b26bbfd78a0cd3a759d6ad7679594cdee611c1899", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:59", "text": "Select the units in which the resolution is defined, either pixels per inch or per centimeter."}
{"id": "76f34fda5507a52d13228e3a7a68ab53957981e9bfcfe91016c3da2b45f6f16b", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:60", "text": "Device Aspect Ratio"}
{"id": "5fb70c46cf658f4e15cd47fe52c7017a5a56bcc222b65b8e4f5d376d0e7b20a1", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:61", "text": "The aspect ratio of your target display (e.g. \"it\" or Maya's Render View)."}
{"id": "390928c8f18762c8c799a895593457144ddc9688078e99f5ee3c27d1ac4eed04", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:62", "text": "Pixel Aspect Ratio"}
{"id": "9a8fe3452de5a9a04f46828b04d043ba66851ac34979079e47648d7a85b2bb68", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:63", "text": "The aspect ratio of the individual pixels of the display device on which you are viewing the rendered image."}
{"id": "21bb0787a96932b9804c2227a3328d01fcc790cec9ca6c60ed7216cd61dbcc74", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:64", "text": "Render Options"}
{"id": "07025a7983a9039f241c427b5e3898631c22282089db7e23cb0d4d7af5b98818", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:65", "text": "Enable Default Light"}
{"id": "25118c4062d07915f9164226ddc000596971e38cae7ea147ed717a28238e0405", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:66", "text": "Turn the default lighting on or off during rendering. Note that we do not render a default light when you have RenderMan lights in the scene"}
{"id": "7b57c84d92eb5b21ca0db9372e2d14a84d74bb5b8b9c145709f57cec0f84cbf8", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:67", "text": "Pre/Post MEL scripts"}
{"id": "a264ca62be3de910b02de88794b8d6291eda7d92c37dbef4799a7a83070034b5", "item_id": "0d8282ff1f:68", "text": "These are fields for entering MEL scripts/commands to be run at the specified times."}
